English Premiership club Newcastle  United have signed US national goalkeeper Brad Friedel for around 250,000  pounds.
Friedel, 23 this week, plays for his college team, UCLA, and has 21  international caps.
The new arrival will compete with Czech, Pavel Srnicek, and Mike Hooper  for the number one shirt at Newcastle, who finished third in the league this  season and hope to qualify for Europe.
United manager, the former England captain Kevin Keegan, said on Friday:  "We have decided that the club needs three quality goalkeepers with the number  of games we will be playing next season."
